    "Notes": {
      "children": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "This class is wrapping the random_rot code from the MDP Toolkit, https://github.com/mdp-toolkit/mdp-toolkit"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Return a random rotation matrix, drawn from the Haar distribution (the only uniform distribution on SO(N)). The algorithm is described in the paper Stewart, G.W., \"The efficient generation of random orthogonal matrices with an application to condition estimators\", SIAM Journal on Numerical Analysis, 17(3), pp. 403-409, 1980. For more information see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthogonal_matrix#Randomization"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "See also the similar "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "ortho_group"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": ". For a random rotation in three dimensions, see "
            },
            {
              "domain": null,
              "role": null,
              "type": "Directive",
              "value": "scipy.spatial.transform.Rotation.random"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "."
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "level": 0,
